quote: And into the forest I go to lose my mind and find my soul.
author: John Muir

quote: The forest is a quiet place if only the best birds sing.
author: Kay Johnson

quote: A grove of giant redwoods or sequoias should be kept just as we keep a great or beautiful cathedral.
author: Theodore Roosevelt

quote: Knowing trees, I understand the meaning of patience. Knowing grass, I can appreciate persistence.
author: Hal Borland

quote: I took a walk in the woods and came out taller than the trees.
author: Henry David Thoreau

quote: The forest is not a resource for us, it is life itself. It is the only place for us to live.
author: Evaristo Nugkuag

quote: In some mysterious way woods have never seemed to me to be static things. In physical terms, I move through them; yet in metaphysical ones, they seem to move through me.
author: John Fowles
